curam.util.persistence

Class DAOImpl<I,E extends Entity<I>,S extends DeepCloneable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.persistence.DAOImpl<I,E,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the identifier type used by both:
    • the logical entity; and
    • the row used to "seed" the entity
    E - the type of entity instances which are created by this class.
    S - the database row from which entity instances are created.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReaderDAO<I,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseDAOImpl, ConcreteDAOImpl

    @Implementable
public abstract class DAOImpl<I,E extends Entity<I>,S extends DeepCloneable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ReaderDAO<I,E>
    Base class for DAO implementations for abstract base classes. Base classes can be read from the database but not created (instead a concrete class must be created). The ID of the entity must also be the ID of the row used to "seed" the entity.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public E get(I id)
        Gets a reference to the entity with the id specified. If the entity required has previously been used in this transaction, it is retrieved from the cache. Such an entity instance may already be more than just a reference - it may have been physically read from the database or even locked. Note that if a reference to a non-existent row is requested, no failure will occur until calling code tries to read the row (via RowManager.getDtls() or TransactionHelper.lock(Entity) ). Of course, there is no guarantee that calling code will ever attempt to read the row, so it is possible that a reference to a non-existent row could survive through to the end of the transaction "undetected".
        Specified by:
        get in interface ReaderDAO<I,E extends Entity<I>>
        Parameters:
        id - The identifier of the entity instance required.
        Returns:
        A reference to the entity with the id specified.

      • getEntity

        protected E getEntity(S row)
        Gets the instance of the entity seeded from the row supplied. If an entity instance seeded on the row has already been created, it will be returned from the entity cache; otherwise a new entity instance will be created in memory and added to the cache. If the row of data is different from that cached, an exception is thrown, since business decisions may have been based on out-of-date data - this can occur if another transaction updates and commits the row during the scope of this transaction.
        Parameters:
        row - The row of data read from the database, used to seed the entity instance.
        Returns:
        The entity instance seeded from the database row supplied.
